      "beat_count": 8,
      "conditioning_notes": "`<CHAR_A>`'s love of making things happen and fear of being seen as all talk drives the \"between the plan and the next plan\" deflection and the instinct to add themselves to `<CHAR_C>`'s new plan — they need to be useful, visibly. `<CHAR_B>`'s love of the next unknown and fear of being stuck drive the sun-navigation beat and the discovery of the trail — they stay oriented even when everyone else unravels, because moving forward is how they cope. `<CHAR_C>`'s love of holding it together and fear of losing control surface in the map dispute and the missing-item spiral — losing a small thing in a Wild location reads as losing the whole situation, which is catastrophic to them. The Wild location keeps everyone alert and reactive; there are no social scripts to fall back on, so each character defaults hard to their core love. The falling arc traces from collective panic through quiet stabilization to a functional (if prickly) truce — tension never fully resolves because the Wild doesn't grant clean endings, only forward motion."
